## Working in this project

This project uses the `research` skill in proposition-first mode. Start from intent in `intake.md`, perform scoping and material/EDA work, record project-level observations in `observations.md`, then use `creating-propositions` inline to create or update `propositions/Pxxx_slug/`. For benchmark or competition work, scoping also precedes baseline/comparator implementation: local file, metric, split, and competition-metadata audits are material, not existing-work scoping. Proposition status determines whether a derived hypothesis is allowed, and each derived hypothesis owns one hypothesis plan under `hypotheses/Hxxx_slug/plan.md`.

Plans declare a category and mode; plans are checked before execution with `research-plan-review`, results are analyzed after execution with `research-result-analysis`, and claims are recorded in the hypothesis plan. State-changing decisions are not global iteration notes: project-wide decisions stay in top-level `decisions.md`, proposition decisions stay in `propositions/Pxxx_slug/decisions.md`, and hypothesis decisions stay in `propositions/Pxxx_slug/hypotheses/Hxxx_slug/decisions.md`.

Research scripts should run through `new_run.py` and leave evidence under `propositions/Pxxx_slug/hypotheses/Hxxx_slug/experiments/runs/<run_id>/`. Print-only output is not a completed result: stdout is not evidence. Each completed run needs `run_manifest.json`, `logs/stdout.log`, `logs/stderr.log`, and at least one manifest-listed durable artifact in `outputs/`, `tables/`, `figures/`, or `intermediate/`. Run `check_run_artifacts.py` before using a run for Result analysis, observations, claims, decisions, or the proposition-level paper.
